An unordered backlog; history lives in docs/plans/, docs/design/, and git.

items
  bart-train-recompute: replace the stored n x draws bart_train block
    (96-99 percent of a large fit object) with on-demand recomputation
    from kept trees through dbarts's exact-replay predict - trades an
    always-paid memory cost for a small per-access compute cost, per
    the general speed/flexibility objective (approved in principle,
    2026-07-16; measurements and framing in
    docs/plans/sample-storage.md). Needs keepTrees semantics, a lazy
    seam behind fitted/extract, and an eager-storage option for
    fast-repeated-access users; no dbarts.h change. If it lands well
    it becomes the reference pattern for other dbarts consumers.
  cleanup-file-names: source-file naming pass (pre-WALNUTS entry,
    still applicable to the surviving files).
  factors-categorical: adopt dbarts's categorical splits instead of
    pinning factors to indicators (the 1.0 port's recorded follow-up).
